From: Luis Gerhorst <luis.gerhorst@fau.de>
Date: Tue, 3 Jun 2025 22:57:54 +0200
Subject: bpf: Return -EFAULT on internal errors
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
Git-commit: 6b84d7895d78079c76c5c7de052d8db3ec6680c9
References: jsc#PED-14653

This prevents us from trying to recover from these on speculative paths
in the future.

Signed-off-by: Luis Gerhorst <luis.gerhorst@fau.de>
Reviewed-by: Eduard Zingerman <eddyz87@gmail.com>
Acked-by: Kumar Kartikeya Dwivedi <memxor@gmail.com>
Acked-by: Henriette Herzog <henriette.herzog@rub.de>
Cc: Maximilian Ott <ott@cs.fau.de>
Cc: Milan Stephan <milan.stephan@fau.de>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250603205800.334980-4-luis.gerhorst@fau.de
Signed-off-by: Alexei Starovoitov <ast@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Hoyeon Lee <hoyeon.lee@suse.com>
---
 kernel/bpf/verifier.c |    6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/kernel/bpf/verifier.c
+++ b/kernel/bpf/verifier.c
@@ -11658,7 +11658,7 @@ static int check_helper_call(struct bpf_
 				verbose(env, "verifier internal error:");
 				verbose(env, "func %s has non-overwritten BPF_PTR_POISON return type\n",
 					func_id_name(func_id));
-				return -EINVAL;
+				return -EFAULT;
 			}
 			ret_btf = btf_vmlinux;
 			ret_btf_id = *fn->ret_btf_id;
@@ -15291,12 +15291,12 @@ static int adjust_reg_min_max_vals(struc
 	if (WARN_ON_ONCE(ptr_reg)) {
 		print_verifier_state(env, vstate, vstate->curframe, true);
 		verbose(env, "verifier internal error: unexpected ptr_reg\n");
-		return -EINVAL;
+		return -EFAULT;
 	}
 	if (WARN_ON(!src_reg)) {
 		print_verifier_state(env, vstate, vstate->curframe, true);
 		verbose(env, "verifier internal error: no src_reg\n");
-		return -EINVAL;
+		return -EFAULT;
 	}
 	err = adjust_scalar_min_max_vals(env, insn, dst_reg, *src_reg);
 	if (err)
